properties.Name: Bar and Board
properties.Notes: 2nd Visit: Clams were fantastic. Brussels were surprisingly good and different than most. Meatball trio was fine. Not bad. Nothing special. Cocktails are good. Not a great whiskey cocktail selection, but cocktails are all good. 1st Visit: We only did mussels and cocktails here. Mussels were pretty solid. Cocktails were good. Kombuchanist was probably the best we had. Flavor appears to change seasonally, but it was good. Good selection of cocktails.

properties.Name: Benjamins Raw Bar
properties.Tags: Bar, Bar Food, Dinner, Lobster Roll, Lunch, Seafood
properties.Notes: 2nd Visit: Lobster rolls are still incredible. Both chowders are also still incredible. 1st Visit: New England Clam Chowder was excellent. Sarah says its ones of the best shes had. The lobster bisque was good. Not great. Rhode Island Clam Chowder was really good. The lobster salad roll was excellent. Definitely would come back for another. The hot butter roll was also good. Not as good as the cold though.

properties.Name: Stoneacre Brasserie
properties.Notes: 2nd Visit: This is a great way to start the day. JUST GET 1 BISCUIT TRIO AND COCKTAILS IN THE FUTURE. It will be a good start to the day without being too filling. Corned beef hash was good. Nothing super special. Biscuits are fantastic. Cocktails are fantastic. 1st Visit: *WE ONLY HAD BRUNCH*. Cocktails were fantastic for brunch. The Pick Me Up was excellent. Very coffee-ey. Really good. Jasmine Milk Punch was really good. A little boozey, but good. The biscuits were excellent. Like, really exceptional biscuits. The biscuit with gravy was really good. The biscuit with butter and jam was really good. We also had the creamy polenta. It was good. Not sure Id order again, but we were expecting something a little different. Was more like grits.

properties.Name: Pizza Service
properties.Notes: After beer, its good. If you need a quick late night snack, this will certainly do. Not great. But fine.

properties.Name: Rooms with a View
properties.Notes: AMAZING LOCATION AND VIEW. Really lovely space. It is loud though. It is in the heart of Ghent and there are a couple bars right across the canal. Still would stay there if we are back in Ghent.

properties.Name: Dufftown Glassworks
properties.Notes: Americano was fine. Nothing special. Not bad. Just a fine americano.

properties.Name: Camilles
properties.Notes: APPETIZERS. Calamari good. Arancini was average. Id order the calamari again, probably would order the arancini. It was fine, not great though. COCKTAILS. Espresso martini was really good. French 75 was excellent. Old fashioned was not good. Cucumber martini was good. Would order all again, except the old fashioned. ENTREES. Ravioli was excellent. Would definitely order again. Risotto was good. Wouldnt order again. Red velvet cheesecake special was really good. Crème brûlée was decent. Bananas foster was ok.

properties.Name: Hula
properties.Notes: Avocado toast was exceptional. Best so far in Edinburgh.

properties.Name: June Coffee
properties.Notes: Best coffee of the trip. Cortado was really good. Iced Latte was really good. Chai was pretty solid. Nothing super special, just a good, slightly spicy chai.

properties.Name: Frites Atelier | Gent
properties.Notes: Best frites on the trip by a long shot. Definitely seems like a tourist trap. Tons of reviews. Always a line. But definitely worth it.

properties.Name: Helen
properties.Notes: Biscuits were incredible. If you go here, you must get these. Yukon Gold Potatoes were good. Definitely not great. A little dry. Would maybe order the potatoes again if I were craving crispy smashed potatoes. Grilled Asparagus was decent. Wouldnt order again. Iberico Presa was very good. Maybe a little overpriced, but I would probably order it again. Peanut Butter Pie was excellent. Definitely would get that again. Good atmosphere. Nice bar to sit at. Not a bad experience and if the menu looks good to you, I would go. I'm not sure I would take another trip though.

properties.Name: Bar Leuv
properties.Notes: BLT was fine. Nothing too special. The Italian Ham toast was fantastic.

properties.Name: The Gather'n Café
properties.Notes: Breaded chicken wrap was good. Cullen soup was good. Nothing is excellent, but there isnt much around so it is a good choice for food.

properties.Name: Coyote Burgers
properties.Notes: Burgers were fine. Milkshakes were good. If you need a change from Scottish food, this is a good option.

properties.Name: The Spoke on Center
properties.Notes: Burgers were pretty good. Food was all pretty good. Their cocktails were very good. The Sweet Potato Tots. were BANGING.

properties.Name: Bard Coffee
properties.Notes: Chai is sweet. Americano is very good. Vietnamese Coffee is good. If you are looking for slightly sweet coffee, its a good choice.

properties.Name: Buzz Coffee
properties.Notes: Chai is very spicy. Americano is very good. Brown sugar latte is good.

properties.Name: Mokabon
properties.Notes: Chai was good, not great. It was on the spicy side, but not crazy. Flat white was solid.

properties.Name: Boga Taco
properties.Notes: Chips and Guac are very good. Chips are homemade and excellent. The guac isnt flashy, but very good. Brad had Barbacoa, carne asada and chorizo. Barbacoa was very good. Best of the 3. Carne asada was a little dry. Chorizo was really good. Sarah had shrimp and carnitas. Shrimp was good. Carnitas was really good. Definitely would order the chorizo, carnitas, and barbacoa again. Shrimp was good enough to order again if you want shrimp. TRIP 2: al pastor is very good. Chicken is good, not great. Currently ranking: 1) Barbacoa 2) Al pastor/carnitas 3) chorizo 4) chicken Queso is good. Nothing special. Not excellent. But if you want queso, it will hit the spot. Cucumber Fresca is banging.

properties.Name: Aux Merveilleux De Fred Bruges
properties.Notes: Chocolate croissant was average. But the chocolate brioche was incredible. The meringue was incredible. Go here and enjoy.

properties.Name: t Eekhoetje
properties.Notes: Chocolate croissant was really good. Apple pie turnover thing was really good. DO NOT GET BREAKFAST. Breakfast was weird and not great. But the pastries are incredible.

properties.Name: Gritty McDuffs
properties.Notes: Clam chowder is solid. French onion soup is good. Nothing special. Lobster poutine is very good.

properties.Name: River House
properties.Notes: Classic tourist trap. Dont be mislead by the reviews. An absolute disgrace to Lobbys across the globe. Extremely overpriced. The seafood chowder was really good. Lobster roll was not great and WAY overpriced. Not fresh. Not much meat. Just very underwhelming.

properties.Name: Luckenbooths
properties.Notes: Cocktails were below average. Not bad but definitely below average. We had a cauliflower and feta soup that was very good. Sunday Roast dinner was good. Not spectacular. Probably can get a Sunday roast better elsewhere. It was definitely good though if you are close and dont want to travel.

properties.Name: The Mooring
properties.Notes: COCKTAILS. French 75 was good. Not great, but good. The Tomcat was fantastic. APPETIZERS. Lobster/Shrimp fritters ok. Definitely wouldnt order again. Not bad though. The sauce was a little too sweet. Kind of just average hush puppies. The clam chowder was very good, not as good as Benjamins. The scallop chowder was very good. Reminded us of Cullen shrink from across the pond. ENTREES. Cold lobster roll was good. Nothing special. Definitely not as good as Benjamins.

properties.Name: Kid Dream Coffee
properties.Notes: Coffee is really good. The chai was really good. More on the spicy side of chais. The Maple Cream Cheese Toast was incredible.

properties.Name: HEX
properties.Notes: Coffee was very good. The Avocado toast was incredible. A much different pairing of flavors than I have had on avocado toast. Everything is slightly Asian inspired. Not the best place to set up and work. Not bad, but definitely not somewhere that I could set up for an entire day.

properties.Name: WAY Specialty Coffee Bar
properties.Notes: Cortado and Flat White are both pretty damn good. Their pastries are also pretty solid. Really good 1-stop-shop to start the day. Chai was not great.

properties.Name: Mornings in Paris
properties.Notes: Cortado was average.

properties.Name: The Coffee Exchange
properties.Notes: Cortado was average. Flat was average. Chai cider was average. Nothing special.

properties.Name: Kaffee Vonsolln
properties.Notes: Cortado was decent. Chocolate Croissant was excellent. It is a crinkled top style. Lots of chocolate.

properties.Name: Solbrun
properties.Notes: Croque Brie was very good. Chocolates were good.

properties.Name: Mackays on the Mile
properties.Tags: Cocktails, Dinner, Lunch, UK Food, Whiskey Bar
properties.Notes: Cullen skink was pretty good. Tomato soup was good. It was pretty thick, so dont expect standard watery tomato water. Scallops were scallops. Nothing special. Fish and chips were the really good. Chips (fries) were crispy and salted. Venison steak was also very good. DEMERIT: They didnt tell us the kitchen was closing and so we werent able to order dessert. Definitely lose some points there.

properties.Name: K & Js Elegant Pastries
properties.Notes: Cupcakes and cookie, not a real bakery. Ice cream, sundaes, cupcakes, milkshakes. GUEST REVIEW (Sydney): Got a chocolate chip cookie cupcake. Extremely sweet. A little too sweet. Good, but definitely not something special.

properties.Name: Deweys
properties.Notes: Decent food. This is definitely a local bar. Cocktails were decent. Nothing special. Side note: this is where I was strongly hit on by a gay cowboy. So if you are into that, he may be there.

properties.Name: Clarke Cooke House
properties.Notes: Definitely a more dressy place. Dont go looking too bummy. The mussels were fantastic. Simple. But really good. The lobster rolls were also really good. Not far behind Benjamins. Cocktails are really good as well. NOTE: The Newport Water is $30. Others were $15. Would go back, but maybe avoid the chaos and grab lunch there.

properties.Name: Rival Bros Coffee
properties.Notes: Derringer is really good. Cortado is good. Great spot for coffee.

properties.Name: Glenfiddich Distillery
properties.Notes: Did not do the tour. Overall vide was not exactly my style. Seemed very uppity. Signage is horrid. Tasting room closed really early. Not my vibe, but the tour may have been excellent.

properties.Name: Beehive Trail
properties.Notes: Difficult. Has a few parts that are pretty sketchy, but it is a really cool hike. If you are capable (somewhat athletic/ok shape) I highly recommend.

properties.Name: Optimist Hall
properties.Notes: Dumpling Lady: Dumplings were REALLY good. Noodles were good, not great. Harriets: Fantastic burger and fries. Sauces are good. Definitely would get this when craving a burger.

properties.Name: El Barrio
properties.Notes: Elote was REALLY good. You can get it on the cob or in a bowl. Definitely order this if you go. Shrimp Quesadilla was good. Nothing super special. Veggie Quesadilla was good. Wouldnt get it again.

properties.Name: Sampan
properties.Notes: Everything was excellent. Cocktails are all great. The Short Rib & Noodles were amazing. The Crispy Duck was amazing. The Short Rib Dumplings were amazing. I would order all of it again. Really good spot.

properties.Name: Kin Khao - Thai Eatery
properties.Notes: Everything was incredible. Their mussels were absolutely fantastic. Everything was great. It is a bit of a weird ordering style though. No a la carte. You pay per person. We paid $50 each and selected 3 apps, 2 entrees and 2 desserts. If you are in the mood for asian while you are in Ghent, this place is an easy recommendation. So damn good.

properties.Name: La Merveilleuse by Infiniti Resorts
properties.Notes: Excellent spot to stay, especially for the price. Close to all the things. Sauna in the room. Would absolutely stay here again.

properties.Name: Restaurant Diligence
properties.Notes: Excellent vibes. Really good spot to have drinks and hang for a little while. Mussels were good, not great. Chocolate Mousse was good. Staff was friendly. Good experience.

properties.Name: Cafe 1496
properties.Notes: Fantastic Chai Latte. Americano is solid. Not spectacular, but good. Avocado toast was great. The tomato, feta, balsamic version was excellent.

properties.Name: Gross Confection Bar
properties.Notes: FEB '23 | Baked Alaska Brownie is Sarahs top dessert on Earth (as of 2/18/23). Key Lime Pie Pavlova is a wonderful light dessert. Flannel Crush cocktail is pretty tasty. Not super bourbon-y. Hot chocolate is really good but a lot. Super super rich. MAR '25 | Still holds up.

properties.Name: N To Tail
properties.Notes: FEB '23 | Crispy rice, fried eggplant and fried chicken app were all fantastic. Green New deal is a great cocktail. Definitely a come back. Only chop sticks (didnt ask for for, but no forks in sight) and a lot of the staff was unfriendly. Our waiter was great, but all other staff that we interacted with was rude. MAR '25 | Still holds up. Much better service this time. Everyone was great.

properties.Name: Blyth & Burrows
properties.Notes: FEB '23 | Great, odd cocktails. MAR '25 | Updated score to 1. Take away cocktails are excellent. We have not had any food.

properties.Name: Lukes Lobster
properties.Notes: FEB '23 | Lobster bisque is very good. Clam chowder is solid. Lobster rolls are all good. Important note: Lobster is cold. Very solid and nice atmosphere. MAR '25 | Still holds up.

properties.Name: Boat Tour | Brugge
properties.Notes: Find a cheap one and do it. Probably wont learn anything, but its a cool way to see the city. Ours was like $15. Definitely worth it.

properties.Name: The Chippy
properties.Notes: Fish and chips were pretty good. Burger is a skip.

properties.Name: Grant Street Bar
properties.Notes: Fish tacos were pretty good. Not sure I would order them again. Friend shrimp and fish sandwich were both good. Consensus was that the shrimp was better. All Panko breaded, not a batter. The pie is worth coming back for. Banana and chocolate cream pie is excellent.

properties.Name: Thank You Thank You
properties.Notes: Flash Brew was really good. One of the better I have ever had. Only had it once though, so I dont know how everything else was.

properties.Name: DEES Specialty Coffee
properties.Notes: Flat white is pretty solid. Chai was good as well. Their standard milk is Oat milk for the chai though. Chocolate croissant was fine.

properties.Name: Take Five Espresso
properties.Notes: Flat white was pretty good. No much better or worse than any others.

properties.Name: Santu Coffee
properties.Notes: Flat white was pretty good. One of the better ones so far.

properties.Name: Empire Coffee
properties.Notes: Flat white was pretty solid. Chocolate croissant was very good. One of the better chocolate croissants I've had. Really good. Chai and London fog are both very good.

properties.Name: Hideout Cafe
properties.Notes: Flat White was really good. Best coffee so far. Chai latte was good. Pretty standard "Starbucks" chai. Also got the Pistachio rose cake which was really good. This place is also a little off the super busy path so it is a nice break from the bustle.

properties.Name: Mon Ami
properties.Notes: Flat white was very good. Nutella filled cookie was very good. Scone was very good. Very nice spot to stop if you are nearly for a quick treat.

properties.Name: De Rechters
properties.Notes: For Belgian food, this is great. The Beef Stew was my favorite of the entire trip. Their Cream and Garlic Mussels were the best regular flavor mussels on the trip.

properties.Name: Howling Wolf Taqueria
properties.Notes: Fried Avocado taco was decent. Nothing special. Queso con carne was solid. Not great. Wing Fiesta quesadilla was pretty good. Would get it again. Margs were decent.

properties.Name: Eugenes Hot Chicken
properties.Notes: Fried Chicken was excellent. I got the Hot. It had just a slight amount of kick. If you like hot at all, this will not be even close to too much heat. Really good. The Mac and Cheese was excellent. Definitely would order again. Cornbread was decent. Not great. Would skip next time. The Banana Pudding was excellent. Definitely would order again. If you like hot chicken, or even just fried chicken, I would say this is a must stop. A few people from BHam told me that this was their favorite of the 3 big name of hot/fried chicken in the area.

properties.Name: The Carron
properties.Notes: Fried fish was really good. Chips (fries) were average. Pineapple fritters were a lot. Not bad. But super rich.

properties.Name: The Stadium
properties.Notes: GO HERE EARLY IN THE WEEK AT 2pm. Get a popover. Change your life. The. Go back every day. Solid coffee. Good breakfast sandwiches. Good cookies. But the popovers will steal your heart. Do not sleep on the popovers.

properties.Name: Liquid Riot
properties.Notes: Good atmosphere. Outdoor seating might be nice in the summer. Cocktails were solid. Nothing special, but good. Great variety (beer + cocktails + food) so nice for a group. VERY IMPORTANT: They have shuffleboard.

properties.Name: Undercurrent Coffee
properties.Notes: Good coffee. Decent workspace, but is definitely a bit tight.

properties.Name: Lions Mound | Waterloo
properties.Notes: Good museum. Wouldnt go out of our way for it, but if you are driving by, it is worth the stop.

properties.Name: Provided Coffee
properties.Notes: Great coffee. Not a place that you can work though.

properties.Name: Ocean Path
properties.Notes: Great first hike. Path along the rocks. You can walk along the rocks basically the entire way. Super easy. If you are looking for a more chill day, there are tons of spoots that you can just sit and hangout on the rocks.

properties.Name: Chez Albert
properties.Notes: Had an original waffle. Very good. Definitely would get again.

properties.Name: The Old Chocolate House
properties.Notes: Hot chocolate is really good. We both got originals. Just pick something that sounds good to you. It will be lovely.

properties.Name: The Bar and Bites Exchange
properties.Notes: Hot toddy is ok. Not a great atmosphere. Very average nachos. If you find yourself here, it wont be great.

properties.Name: Prevail Union
properties.Notes: Iced Latte was good. A little better than Cala.

properties.Name: Cala Coffee
properties.Notes: Iced latte was good. Nothing extraodinary, but would go back.

properties.Name: Santos Coffee
properties.Notes: Iced Latte was ok. Chai was ok. If you are in that section of businesses or at the convention center, it is definitely good enough to get. You wont be disappointed, but you also wont be blown away. Think Starbuck-ish

properties.Name: The Citadel | Dinant
properties.Notes: If you are in Dinant, definitely do it. Worth the money. Really immersive. Maybe too much so.

properties.Name: High Roller Lobster Company
properties.Notes: If you are in old port, go here. Lobster ghee, lime Mayo, and jalapeño Mayo are all good. Sweet potato fries are really good.

properties.Name: Project Social
properties.Notes: If you are into cocktails and sitting outside, this is a great pregame spot or just a spot to sit and chill with a drink. Pita and assorted dips were really good.

properties.Name: The Male Hunter
properties.Notes: If you are passing and need a coffee, fine. Definitely not good coffee. Also, I dont think he offers Take-Away.

properties.Name: Glen Rowan Cafe
properties.Notes: If you are passing, this is a nice little spot for coffee. Their baked goods looked good.

properties.Name: Raven Room
properties.Notes: If you like cocktails, this is the spot. Very cool atmosphere. And the bartenders are legit. If you dont see something on the menu that you like, you can describe what you are feeling and they will make you something delicious.

properties.Name: Breakers Tour
properties.Notes: It was definitely cool if you are into those kinds of things. The details throughout are incredible. Nothing was incredibly well labeled though.

properties.Name: Midtown Grill
properties.Notes: Its a tourist spot. Come here to grab an "in between" meal with a beer. You arent getting anything great or even good, but you've got a seat right on the water to enjoy a beer.

properties.Name: Geddys
properties.Notes: Just a solid restaurant. Definitely a popular one among tourists. But good.

properties.Name: IzyCoffee Leuven
properties.Notes: Just not good. Not a great flat white. Chai was flat out bad.

properties.Name: Melt
properties.Notes: Just skip it.

properties.Name: Graffiti Bar
properties.Notes: Kantoi Road was fantastic. Mule was great. All the cocktails were really good. I would order them all again. The small plates were also great. Crab Wontons were delicious. Had a nice real crab flavor. The Kobe Sliders were also really good.

properties.Name: Last Call Baking Company
properties.Notes: Legitimately one of the better bakeries I have ever been too. Gochujang Twist is very strange, but REALLY good. Croissants/Almond Croissant are definitely among the best I've had. Really, anything with that croissant dough was incredible. The Danish was really good. Cornbread with swiss merengue was really good. The Coffee Swirl was incredible. Everything we had was really good. Definitely a spot you need to go to. If it sounds interesting, order it. It will be good.

properties.Name: The Nitro Bar
properties.Notes: Light roast flash brew was excellent. Chai latte was excellent. Not super spicey but you could still taste the chai. Tacos were fine. Probably wouldnt order them again. Cortado was good. Lemon poppyseed muffin and blueberry muffins were both pretty good.

properties.Name: Bar Harbor Cheescake Company
properties.Notes: Little mini cheesecakes. Lots of options. All pretty solid. Nothing mind blowing, but a nice spot for dessert.

properties.Name: Bobs Clam Hut
properties.Notes: Lobster Roll was solid. Lobster tasted fresh. Roll is basic, but really good. The Lobster Stew is incredible. I would go out of the way for it. I'll be missing this soup…

properties.Name: Side Street Cafe
properties.Notes: Lobster Stew is solid. This is not a bisque so dont expect that. But it is very good.

properties.Name: Villanis Bakery
properties.Notes: Lobster Tail. Holy shit. Gotta get it. Chocolate croissant was fantastic. Almond croissant was pretty solid. Pistachio cheesecake was good, not great. Tiramisu was pretty solid.

properties.Name: Elephantine Bakery
properties.Notes: London Fog was really good. Chai was decent. Cortado was average. Too much milk. Chocolate Croissant and Pistachio Croissant are excellent. All the pastries we had were really good. Chocolate chip cookie was god, not great. Madeline was average.

properties.Name: Springline Coffee
properties.Notes: London fogs were pretty solid. Empire is better, but not worth the walk back up the hill just for the drink.

properties.Name: La Maison Navarre
properties.Notes: Macarons were decent. Other pastries looked good, but we only had macarons.

properties.Name: Poules Moules
properties.Notes: Mussels were good. Beef stew was good. Creme brûlée was good. Everything was good, not great. Would definitely get it again. Vibes were really good in there.

properties.Name: Hotel Jan Brito
properties.Notes: Nice room. Really close to everything. Parking is close. Solid option.

properties.Name: Giddy Goat Coffee Roasters
properties.Notes: Nice work vibes. Decent coffee. Decent empanadas.

properties.Name: Royal Mile
properties.Notes: Not a bad place to stay. There is a lot to do in this area, but definitely Explore outside of here.

properties.Name: Standard Baking Co
properties.Notes: Not a scone place. Chocolate Rye cookie is very good. Chocolate croissant is very good.

properties.Name: Trailhead Public House and Eatery
properties.Notes: Not bad. Nothing special though. I dont think anyone was unhappy with their meal, but definitely nothing special.

properties.Name: FritBar
properties.Notes: Nothing special. Fries were fine. Options were good.

properties.Name: Night Swim
properties.Notes: Only got the flash brew. Not my favorite. Looks like they are going to be similar to Queen City Grounds.

properties.Name: Aberlour Distillery
properties.Notes: Only got to stop in the shop. Experience was ok. They didnt charge for samples, which is always excellent. Not a ton of room for anything. Nowhere to sit or hangout.

properties.Name: Boulangerie Kempinaire
properties.Notes: Only had a chocolate croissant. It was good. Not great. The bread looked excellent though.

properties.Name: Kaffeeology
properties.Notes: Only had a cortado. It was average. Seemed like a place that is better for lattes. They have milkshakes also.

properties.Name: Peppers Seafood Co
properties.Notes: Only had a Lobster Roll. Over-dressed. Lobster was good, but the roll was just not great.

properties.Name: Wentworth & Fenn
properties.Notes: Overall, everything was good. Nothing was spectacular. Oatmeal cookie sandwich was good. Gingerbread cookie sandwich was good. Bread pudding was decent.

properties.Name: Ting Thai Caravan
properties.Notes: Pad See-Ew was really good. Nothing incredibly special, but really good. Thai Green Curry was really good. One of the better Green Curries Sarah has had. She added shrimp and coconut rice. We also had the Goong Frong Beer. Those were fine. Nothing special. Probably would skip those and try something else next time.

properties.Name: Kultur Bakery
properties.Notes: Pastries were all pretty good. Nice staff. Good selection.

properties.Name: Kilwins
properties.Notes: Peanut butter cup was decent. Chocolate covered shortbread was ok. Hot chocolate was good. If you need sweets, not a bad option. But definitely nothing great.

properties.Name: Giuseppes - Pizza Forno a Legna
properties.Notes: Pizza was fine. Wouldnt choose it again, but it was a fine meal.

properties.Name: Sloss Furnace
properties.Notes: Pretty cool area to walk around. I think it may be a paid venue during the day. We had an event there and it was fantastic. There are excellent stories about Dr. Daniel Saint Sloss and the piss puck paint factories run by alien-fed yoked hamsters here. Really cool venue.

properties.Name: Queen City Grounds
properties.Notes: Pretty solid experience. Cool vibes to work. Coffee was pretty solid.

properties.Name: Moab Garage
properties.Notes: Pretty sure we stopped here most days. Croque Monsieur was delightful. Garage Burrito got great reviews. Biscuits and Gravy were good. This spot was pretty busy, but very good. The cubanos are very nice. I had a TON of them while out in Moab.

properties.Name: Soupr
properties.Notes: Really good lunch spot. Caesar sandwich was good. Soups were all good. Really good for a lighter lunch.

properties.Name: Lunch
properties.Notes: Really solid deli sandwiches.

properties.Name: Chieftain Hotel Restaurant
properties.Notes: Red pepper soup and roll were very good. Fried fish was pretty solid. Fries (chips) were average. Tartar sauce was excellent in Bradleys opinion. Pretty good in Sarahs opinion. Sticky Toffee Pudding was average.

properties.Name: Ono Poke
properties.Notes: Salmon and Tuna Crunch bowl was really good. Definitely would get again. It is in a food hall with several options that looked good.

properties.Name: Balmoral Castle Cafe
properties.Notes: Sandwiches were decent. Scone was pretty solid. If you are at the castle and hungry, it will do the job. Definitely not special.

properties.Name: Barrazza cafe
properties.Notes: Sandwiches were fine. Beer selection was really good. Would go back for a beer, not for food. They have a few tables by the water. Decent vibe.

properties.Name: Blount Clam Shack
properties.Notes: Sarah had the mayo lobster roll. Bradley had the warm butter tossed lobster roll. Both were solid. Nothing special, but if you arent super experienced in the lobster roll world, this is great. Plenty of meat. Blount clam chowder was good, again nothing special. Seafood was really good. Super rich though. Definitely a shareable.

properties.Name: Down East Deli
properties.Notes: Sarahs favorite Lobster Rolls in Bar Harbor. They have Mayo and butter style. Both are very good.

properties.Name: Havana
properties.Notes: Seafood Paella was very good. This is a great spot for a fancier dinner.

properties.Name: Simple Merchant Coffee
properties.Notes: Shakerato was really good. Would definitely order this again. Baked goods were average.

properties.Name: Gross Bakery
properties.Notes: Shortbread is good. Everything Croissant cream cheese is excellent.

properties.Name: Bull Feeneys
properties.Notes: Solid choice. Not a must stop. Expensive for what it is. Great atmosphere. Fried pickles are delightful. Seafood chowder is solid. Not great. But solid. Fish and chips is solid. Not great. Shepherds pie is solid.

properties.Name: Jeannies Great Maine Breakfast
properties.Notes: Solid food. Nothing mind blowing.

properties.Name: Newport Sandwich Co
properties.Notes: Soup was pretty solid. The roast beef sandwiches were pretty underwhelming. I think some of the other sandwiches could be good, but there are plenty of other good restaurants in the area.

properties.Name: Black Isle Bar
properties.Notes: Spider monkey IPA was good. Red Kite Ale was good. If you are anywhere near this, it is a good choice. It is worth the 10-15 minute drive from Glencoe if you are stopped there exploring. Ndjuda and honey pizza was really good. Primavera was really good.

properties.Name: The Isle Inn
properties.Notes: Steak and Ale Pie was decent. Not bad. Nothing special though. Cullen Skink was excellent. Cheesy Garlic bread was surprisingly good.

properties.Name: Greyfriars Bobbys Bar
properties.Tags: Cocktails, Lunch, Pub Food, UK Food
properties.Notes: Steak and ale pie was pretty good. Cullen Skink was good. Elderflower Spritz was very refreshing and delightful. Floradora was also very good. Would highly recommend both for light, refreshing drinks. This feels like a great spot for lunch, but probably wouldnt waste a dinner on it.

properties.Name: Mill Street Inn
properties.Notes: Super friendly staff. Great vibes in our room. Exposed brick with high ceilings in the room. Sangria in the lobby. Nespresso in the room. Bathroom was a little small. Pillows were WAY too soft. The bed was comfortable. Definitely on the soft side though. Parking was available as well. A little tight, but available.

properties.Name: Jim Reed Book Store
properties.Notes: Super interesting store. If you are into books or just old shit, go here. He has books that are 500+ years old. It is a little chaotic when you walk in, but the owner is super nice and willing to chat/help. Super interesting.

properties.Name: Benromach Distillery
properties.Notes: Super small place. Very cool to see this compared to the others. Great tour. Product was great. Gave free samples of things after the tour, like beyond the standard 2 which was great for deciding what I wanted to purchase. Highly recommend.

properties.Name: Koto Sushi
properties.Notes: Sushi was surprisingly great. The Gyoza was also fantastic. I would absolutely go back here again. It was slow during lunch too, so it could be a great lunch spot.

properties.Name: El Vez
properties.Notes: The Baja Shrimp tacos were pretty good. The Marg was fantastic. Guac was good. Vibes were really good.

properties.Name: Le Pain Quotidien
properties.Notes: The chocolate croissant was good. Nothing special.

properties.Name: Chez Bouboule
properties.Notes: The dijonaise mussels were incredible. If you go here, find a flavor that sounds nice to you and get the mussels. So damn good. Tiramisu was pretty solid as well.

properties.Name: Prunella
properties.Notes: The Hot Honey pizza was really good. That was the only thing that I had, but everyone else at the table seemed to enjoy their dish.

properties.Name: Gasta
properties.Notes: The Jimmey 2.0 was really good. The #4 pizza was also very good (had salami and hot honey). Would definitely go back. It does close at 5 though. Which is massively annoying for a bar.

properties.Name: The Red Parrot
properties.Notes: The menu here is huge. Like Cheesecake Factory big. Plenty of options for everyone. We had Lobster Rangoons. They were decent. Not very lobster-ey. Not bad. Also had the Bananas Francesca dessert. Nothing special. Not bad.

properties.Name: Birch
properties.Notes: The Millionaire Shortbread is one of the greatest bars you will eat. The flat white is good. The chai is good. The bean toast was surprisingly easy incredible. The chorizo and egg was incredible. The ricotta and olive was really good if you want something lighter. The beetroot was good, but a little sweeter. Everything is good.

properties.Name: Himschoot
properties.Notes: Their breads looked really good. Chocolate croissant was fine. Not great. Not bad.

properties.Name: Hi-Wire Brewing
properties.Notes: They have shuffleboard, ping pong, corn hole and a few other games. Really large and open space with a nice outdoor area. The Pink Lemonade Sour was really good. GUEST RATING (Sydney): Margarita Sour was ok. A little too beer-ey for a sour. The Pickle Sour was good. Would order again (if you like pickle).

properties.Name: Bubble Rock
properties.Notes: This is a really cool off-shoot of the Jordan Pond loop. It has a couple slightly challenging "bouldering" areas, but nothing crazy. Highly recommend.

properties.Name: Antica Forma
properties.Notes: This is absolutely a tourist trap. Food was very average. Service was not good. Drinks were average. And it was quite expensive, given the experience. Defintily skip this.

properties.Name: Galyns
properties.Notes: This is one definitely popular, but was a bit underwhelming, especially for the price.

properties.Name: Dunnotar Castle
properties.Notes: This may have been the coolest spot we saw on the trip. This is super cool. We didnt get to to do the tour, but it was just a cool spot to check out. Highly recommend.

properties.Name: Roma Ristorante
properties.Notes: This place was pretty cool. Little Italian corner store. The pizza was pretty solid. I'm sure there is better in the area, but this was good. The Lobster Tail pastry was incredible. They had a nice selection of pastries.

properties.Name: Picnic
properties.Tags: Bakery, Breakfast, Cafe, Coffee, Lobster Roll, Lunch
properties.Notes: THIS RATING IS BASED ONLY ON THE PASTRIES.

properties.Name: Quesadilla Mobilla
properties.Notes: This was a few of our favorite places in Moab. Those quadillas were incredible.

properties.Name: Thai Bella Moab
properties.Notes: This was everyone favorite dinner. So darn good. If you like Thai, this is a must stop.

properties.Name: Xtreme 4x4 Tours
properties.Notes: This was super cool. We did the 2.5 Hour U-Drive Tour. It was a ton of fun. A little pricey, but worth it in our opinions. At the beginning, it definitely gave us all a "what the hell did we just sign up for" feeling, but that quickly disappears and it was a ton of fun. This took you through the old dunes. SUPER cool. Very strange terrain that I dont think you really get anywhere else while you are out there.

properties.Name: Rocksalt
properties.Notes: Vegan Avocado Toast was really good, but pretty heavy. Not in a "super filling" way, but just kind of oily. Really good though. The Salmon Avocado Toast was good. The rest of the food sounded really good. I would probably order something different next time. Has potential to be a Go Back for sure.

properties.Name: Go.fre Gent
properties.Notes: Waffle was probably the best that we had. Only had the Original with nothing on it. Also had their Meringue. It was pretty decent. If you are looking for a Liege waffle, this is probably the spot to go.

properties.Name: Balmoral Castle
properties.Notes: Was a pretty cool area to stop. If you are into any royal things, it was a pretty cool spot to go.

properties.Name: Bar Harbor Lobster Co
properties.Notes: WAY better food for the price. Definitely a tourist trap.

properties.Name: Glenlevit Distillery
properties.Notes: We did not do the tour. The vibe is excellent. Cocktails were good. Everyone was super friendly. The bar was large and wonderful for hanging out.

properties.Name: Bonjour Bakery & Café
properties.Notes: We discovered this one late in our trip. Must stop for sure. Everything we got from there was wonderful. If you like pastries and baked goods, you gotta stop here.

properties.Name: Portsmouth Gas Light
properties.Notes: We got pizza to go. Very solid pizza. If you are looking for something after everything else closes, this is a great option. We have the Gas Light and would definitely get it again.

properties.Name: Row 34
properties.Notes: We had apps. Oysters were really good. Fresh. Shrimp cocktail was really good. Sauces were all really good. Mussels were good. Biscuit was really good. Very large. Calamri was fine. Wouldnt order it again.

properties.Name: Bonny Breads
properties.Notes: We had the chocolate chip cookie and chocolate croissant. Both pretty decent. Nothing extraordinary. They had several other options that looked really good though.

properties.Name: Loudons
properties.Notes: We had the Hot Filled Sausage roll. Skip it. Sausage is very good, but as an item, the roll is just not great. Big let down. The Korean Benny was pretty solid though. Flat white was good. Not great. Chai was good. Not great. This is a great spot if you cant get in anywhere else, but there are far better places to go.

properties.Name: Noble
properties.Notes: We only had beer. Great place to sit. I dont feel confident that the food is good.

properties.Name: Grand Cafe at the Scotsman
properties.Notes: We only had dessert and cocktails here, but the food menu looked pretty solid. COCKTAILS. Almond and Berries cocktail was incredible. Tasted like a fruit roll up and had a very pretty glass. Malt and Mango cocktail was also good if you like mango. DESSERTS. Whiskey Ginger Pudding was pretty decent. Celebration of Strawberries was super light and refreshing.

properties.Name: No. 1 High Street
properties.Tags: Bar Food, Dinner, Pub Food, UK Food
properties.Notes: We only had desserts and a whiskey flight. Cranachan was ok. Sticky Toffee Pudding was pretty good. Overall vibe wasnt great. Bar didnt have cocktails. No list of beers or whiskey. Just overall not great vibes. Felt like a tourist trap. Its wasnt bad, but there are definitely plenty of places better.

properties.Name: Scialo Brothers Bakery
properties.Notes: We only had the cannoli, but it was pretty average. Not a great selection. Probably skip this.

properties.Name: The Co-op
properties.Notes: Well this is an interesting one. Not a restaurant. But you will almost certainly find yourself here for a dinner. The frozen pizzas that look boujee are in fact good. The sticky toffee pudding in the dark box is also really good. Like oddly good. One of the better of the trip.

properties.Name: Cadillac Mountain Sunrise
properties.Notes: You will need to schedule this through the link. Be prepared for cold and wind. Get there early. Bring blankets/other things to get comfy.

properties.Name: Gran kaffee de Passage
properties.Notes: This place was incredible. The ribs were fantastic. The beef stew was incredible. Defintiely a great place to stop
